.TH "decodeURIComponent" "JS" "February 21, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
decodeURIComponent - decodeURIComponent()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]decodeURIComponent()\f[B]\f[R] function decodes a Uniform
Resource Identifier (URI) component previously created by
\f[CR]encodeURIComponent()\f[R] or by a similar routine.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
decodeURIComponent(encodedURI)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]encodedURI\f[R]
An encoded component of a Uniform Resource Identifier.
.SS Return value
A new string representing the decoded version of the given encoded
Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) component.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]URIError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]encodedURI\f[R] contains a \f[CR]%\f[R] not followed by
two hexadecimal digits, or if the escape sequence does not encode a
valid UTF-8 character.
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[CR]decodeURIComponent()\f[R] is a function property of the global
object.
.PP
\f[CR]decodeURIComponent()\f[R] uses the same decoding algorithm as
described in \f[CR]decodeURI()\f[R].
It decodes \f[I]all\f[R] escape sequences, including those that are not
created by \f[CR]encodeURIComponent\f[R], like
\f[CR]-.!\[ti]*\[aq]()\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Decoding a Cyrillic URL component
.IP
.EX
decodeURIComponent(\[dq]JavaScript_%D1%88%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%BB%D1%8B\[dq]);
// \[dq]JavaScript_шеллы\[dq]
.EE
.SS Catching errors
.IP
.EX
try {
  const a = decodeURIComponent(\[dq]%E0%A4%A\[dq]);
} catch (e) {
  console.error(e);
}

// URIError: malformed URI sequence
.EE
.SS Decoding query parameters from a URL
\f[CR]decodeURIComponent()\f[R] cannot be used directly to parse query
parameters from a URL.
It needs a bit of preparation.
.IP
.EX
function decodeQueryParam(p) {
  return decodeURIComponent(p.replace(/\[rs]+/g, \[dq] \[dq]));
}

decodeQueryParam(\[dq]search+query%20%28correct%29\[dq]);
// \[aq]search query (correct)\[aq]
.EE
